remove git from project 
-------------------------
step 1 :-  go to settings from file > settings > version control > select git root then remove it and apply > ok     
---------

step 2 :-  then in terminal go to project location ---> rm -rf $(find . -name ".git*")
---------

---------------------------------------------------------*********************************--------------------------------------

	add git repo to project 
      --------------------------

https://docs.github.com/en/github/importing-your-projects-to-github/importing-source-code-to-github/adding-an-existing-project-to-github-using-the-command-line

      
step 1 --> go to terminal in android studio --> (type) git init  --> to initialize repository

step 2 --> then check -->  git status

step 3 --> stage the files using --> git add -A  (or) git add filename

step 4 --> commit using -->  git commit -a

step 5 --> now to make it a remote repo create a new repo in github then copy the http link of the repo then create a key and use that key as a password for the push 

step 6 --> git remote -m  



_----------------------------------------------**************__________________________-------------------------------------------

   create a token for github (PAT - personal access token)
 ----------------------------
  
   
https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/keeping-your-account-and-data-secure/creating-a-personal-access-token




